> Unfortunately, disruptive innovation theory isn‚Äôt entirely reliable, as explained in the [New Yorker](https://link.morningbrew.com/click/31713240.358489/aHR0cHM6Ly9saW5rcy5tb3JuaW5nYnJldy5jb20vYy83TXM%5FbWJjaWQ9MzE3MTMyNDAuMzU4NDg5Jm1pZD1hN2EzMGZkMzMwOGQ5MThlOWJjZDYwYTcxOTM1NmE2NCZtYmxpZD0yNTAyZjdjMzczMDg/647f57557909890704100155B48608468). For example, Christensen predicted in 2007 that the iPhone would be a failure for Apple. Better luck next time!
